SIMPLE: hell
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hell
<hw>Hell</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>hell</ets>;
akin to D. <ets>hel</ets>, OHG. <ets>hella</ets>, G.
<ets>h⟦oum⟧lle</ets>, Icel. <ets>hal</ets>, Sw. <ets>helfvete</ets>,
Dan. <ets>helvede</ets>, Goth. <ets>halja</ets>, and to AS.
<ets>helan</ets> to conceal. <?/<?/<?/. Cf. <er>Hele</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>, <er>Conceal</er>, <er>Cell</er>, <er>Helmet</er>,
<er>Hole</er>, <er>Occult</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The place of the dead, or of souls after death; the
grave; -- called in Hebrew <xex>sheol</xex>, and by the Greeks
<xex>hades</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He descended into <qex>hell</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Book of Common
Prayer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou wilt not leave my soul in <qex>hell</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
xvi. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The place or state of punishment for the wicked
after death; the abode of evil spirits. Hence, any mental torment;
anguish.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Within him <xex>hell</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is a knell⟦br⟧
That summons thee to heaven or to <qex>hell</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A place where outcast persons or things are
gathered</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A dungeon or prison; also, in
certain running games, a place to which those who are caught are carried
for detention.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A gambling house.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
convenient little gambling <xex>hell</xex> for those who had grown
reckless.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>W. Black.</au> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A place into which
a tailor throws his shreds, or a printer his broken type.</def>
<au>Hudibras.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gates of hell</b></col>. <fld>(Script.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Gate</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 4.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hell</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hell
<hw>Hell</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To overwhelm.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hellanodic</ent>⟦br⟧
